{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Varoma into position and weigh in eggplant slices. Place slices around sides of Varoma dish, sprinkle with 1 tsp salt and continue salting each layer until all eggplant is used. Set aside for 30 minutes. Grease a casserole dish (9 in. x 13 in.) and 2 baking sheets and set aside.","Place cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic, parsley and peppercorns into mixing bowl and grate <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add onion and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add oil and beef, break into pieces with spatula and sauté <b>3 min\/212°F\/\/speed <b>.","Add tomatoes, wine, oregano, cinnamon, 1 tsp salt, cayenne and ⅛  tsp nutmeg and cook <b>20 min\/212°F\/\/speed <b>. Meanwhile, rinse eggplant in cold water to remove excess salt. Gently pat dry with paper towels. Place eggplant slices onto baking sheets and lightly brush with oil, season with 1 tsp salt and ¼ tsp ground pepper. Broil in oven 2 minutes each side flipping so both sides are tender and golden brown.","Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange eggplant slices in casserole dish. Cover eggplant with meat sauce. No need to clean mixing bowl.","Place butter, milk, flour, eggs and ¼ tsp ground pepper into mixing bowl and cook <b>8 min\/195°F\/speed 4<b>. Adjust seasoning to taste.","Add 2 oz reserved grated cheese and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Cover meat layer with white sauce, top with remaining grated cheese and lightly sprinkle with ⅛ tsp nutmeg. Bake 30 minutes (400°F). Allow Moussaka to rest for 10 minutes to firm then cut into squares and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["48 oz eggplant, cut into ¼ in. slices (approx. 3 large eggplants)","3 tsp fine sea salt, divided, to taste","4 oz Parmigiano Reggiano, cut into pieces","½ oz garlic cloves (approx. 5 cloves)","½ oz fresh parsley, leaves and tender stems (approx. ½ bunch)","½ tsp black peppercorns","9 oz yellow onions, halved (approx. 2 medium onions)","1 oz olive oil","16 oz ground beef","8 oz canned crushed tomatoes","4 oz red wine","1 tsp dried oregano","¼ tsp ground cinnamon","&frac18; tsp cayenne pepper","¼ tsp ground nutmeg, divided, to taste","olive oil, to brush","½ tsp ground black pepper, divided, to taste","4 oz salted butter, plus extra for greasing","24 oz whole milk","2 ½ oz all-purpose flour","2 large eggs"]}],"id":"r157094","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-U0wYwRC0rk4\/XZQxQZg17yI\/AAAAAAAActQ\/hqx7DUmaGtMJ_o3X99QNQ7FnYq2u89mvgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_omzvOuffvFIO_wv1.png","title":"Moussaka","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"15 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"1506 kJ \/ 360 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, paper towels, pastry brush, casserole dish (9 in. x 13 in.), baking sheets, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Nutmeg has a delicate, spicy flavor that starts to dissipate shortly after being ground. Grinding your own results in more flavor from a smaller amount. You can freshly grind a whole nutmeg for this recipe. Prior to grinding the cheese, place nutmeg into mixing bowl and grind <strong>1 min\/speed 9<\/strong>. Transfer to bowl and set aside or store in an airtight container."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","2h 20m","1 portion"]}